    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>186</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>102000</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2018"/>, pp. <citedRange>279-280</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/> <citedRange>68.1750</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#_ος"><gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character" precision="low"/><seg part="F"><supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor"><choice><unclear>χ</unclear><unclear>κ</unclear></choice></supplied>ος</seg></name><space quantity="1" unit="character"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63642"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἐλαιίτας">Ἐλαιίτα</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem><gap reason="lost" quantity="6" unit="character" precision="low"/><supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor"><choice><unclear>χ</unclear><unclear>κ</unclear></choice></supplied>ος<space quantity="1" unit="character"/></lem>
                    <rdg resp="#SECir"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><choice><unclear>κ</unclear><unclear>χ</unclear></choice>ος</rdg>
                </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>kos (ou khos) fils d'Elaiitas.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>kos (or chos) son of Elaiitas.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>kos (o chos) figlio di Elaiitas.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This Elaiitas might be the son of the priest who dedicated a bench on the Fountain Terrace (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr080500</ref>) and, in Rosamilia's view, he would be the uncle 
                    of the priest of the same name mentioned at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr096700</ref>, line 4.</p>
                <p>The first letter partly seen by G. Pugliese Carratelli (<bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>186</citedRange></bibl>) was not visible to C. Dobias-Lalou in 2001 nor can it be traced on the squeeze.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
